## 2026-04-04 - Core resolver formula unit extraction silently falls back to 'px'/'ms' when extractFormulaUnit returns null
- Two improvements made to `resolver.ts`:
  1. **Bare-number dimension/duration normalization**: Extended the typed-value reconstruction block (formerly formula-only) to also wrap bare-number dimension/duration tokens (e.g. `{$type:"dimension", $value:8}`) into `{value:8, unit:'px'}` / `{value:200, unit:'ms'}` objects. Condition changed from `isFormula(token.$value)` guard to `$type === 'dimension' || $type === 'duration'` guard, with `isFormulaSrc` used only for the unit-extraction call.
  2. **`extractFormulaUnit` type-based inference**: Added Strategy 2 — when a referenced token's resolved `$value` is a plain number (not a `{unit}` object), check `resolved.$type`. If 'dimension' return 'px'; if 'duration' return 'ms'. This removes the `?? 'px'` / `?? 'ms'` hardcoded fallbacks as the primary mechanism — the unit is now inherited from the referenced token's type rather than hardcoded at the call site. The `??` fallbacks remain as a last resort for pure-number arithmetic formulas with no dimension/duration refs.

